      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2606.00060",
      "use": "Supports explicit cost-aware abstention and walk-forward evaluation. It also reports that tree boosting was descriptively stronger than tested neural alternatives without establishing statistical dominance."
    },
    {
      "title": "Deep Limit Order Book Forecasting",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2403.09267",
      "use": "Requires transaction-level practicality and after-cost evidence rather than treating forecast classification metrics as a trading result."
